definitions.definition: An artificial channel that is constructed to convey water from one location to another.
A structure carrying water over a river or depression, especially an ancient structure.
A structure conveying fluid, such as the cerebral aqueduct or vestibular aqueduct .

main_definition: An artificial channel that is constructed to convey water from one location to another.

( anatomy ) A structure conveying fluid, such as the cerebral aqueduct or vestibular aqueduct .
